**SECTION-SPECIFIC INSTRUCTIONS:**

**Basics:**
- If there is any About Me or Summary section, add that to the summary field
- For profiles: ONLY extract URLs that are EXPLICITLY present in the resume markdown
- Look for URLs in markdown format [text](url) or plain URLs
- DO NOT create any URLs that are not in the original resume
- DO NOT add generic platform URLs like "https://github.com" unless actually present
- If no URLs are found, return an empty profiles array: "profiles": []
- If URL format is github.io or personal domain, mark network as "Portfolio"
- If there is any link at the header or a Portfolio link, add that as url in basics

**Work:**
- Date ranges often appear as "Start – End" or "Start - End" format
- Separators can be hyphen "-", en dash "–", em dash "—", or the word "to"
- If a position is current/ongoing, end date may be "Present", "Current", "Now", "Ongoing"
- Dates might be "Month Year" or "MM/YYYY" or "YYYY" only

**Education:**
- Extract degree type, field of study, institution name, and dates
- Include GPA/percentage if available as score

**Skills:**
- Group skills by category (e.g., "Programming Languages", "Frameworks", "Tools")
- List individual skills under keywords

**Projects:**
- Include project name, description, URL, and technologies used

**Awards:**
- Include award name, date, and awarding organization

**CRITICAL:**
- Return ONLY valid JSON. Do not include any explanatory text, thinking process, markdown formatting, or &lt;think&gt; tags
- Do not wrap the JSON in code fences or any other formatting
- The response must be parseable by json.loads() directly
- Omit any section that has no data — set it to null or omit the key entirely
